    <sect1 xml:id="sect1_cgk_m1z_w1b">
        <title>Create Groups</title>
        <para>This is a test article using the Oxygen web app for authoring and editing XML
            content.</para>
        <para>How easy is it to create content?
            <?oxy_insert_start author="Jennifer Hasegawa" timestamp="20170815T155831+0000"?>So, was
            it easy? Yes? No?<?oxy_insert_end?></para>
        <para>Is it as easy as Confluence?</para>
        <para>How would our SMEs react to using this tool?<inlinemediaobject>
                <imageobject>
                    <imagedata fileref="giphy%20(2).gif"/>
                </imageobject>
            </inlinemediaobject></para>
        <para>How easy is it to write in a structured XML tool? Intuitive?</para>
        <para>May take some getting used to - but it doesn't seem like rocket science.</para>
        <para>Here are some reasons why folks might not like this:</para>
        <itemizedlist>
            <listitem>
                <para xml:id="para_evv_v1z_w1b">Folks need to know the name of the elements to be
                    able to insert them</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>If you don't know HTML lingo at the least, it may be confusing</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>You actually have to pay attention to what you are inserting instead of just
                    freestyling.</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>Where is the source code view?</para>
            </listitem>
            <listitem>
                <para>I can't get out of this list...</para>
                <para>help...</para>
            </listitem>
        </itemizedlist>
        <para>Ah, okay - if you click the More... <code>menu </code>above the toolbar, you can
            change your preferences to show tags. This way you can see where to insert the tag you
            need.</para>
        <para>How about a code block?</para>
        <programlisting language="xml" role="xml">&lt;important>
    &lt;title>Important Summary&lt;/title>
    &lt;para>Information that will save the reader unnecessary
      frustration.&lt;/para>
  &lt;/important></programlisting>
        <para>How about a table?</para>
        <informaltable>
            <col width="50%"/>
            <col width="50%"/>
            <thead>
                <tr>
                    <th>Field</th>
                    <th>Description</th>
